Then, converting this to a list, the `i`-th element of the list will be the same as the `i`-th element of the vector.

Similarly, `v.toList` is the list of elements. Then, `v.toList.set (↑idx) elt` is the list where the `↑idx`-th element is `elt`. So, if `i = ↑idx`, then the `i`-th element is `elt`. Otherwise, it's the same as the `i`-th element of `v.toList`.

